      "writtenOn": "2019-10-18T16:03:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I went and stepped through the code and can confirm that as the CTFont is created it first gets all the right variations from the CGFont passed in but then, as a very last step, it overwrites the \u0027opsz\u0027 axis value with the size passed here. I took a look and every CTFontCreate* function takes a size parameter which is used this way. As a result, I don\u0027t think there is currently any way to properly specify the \u0027opsz\u0027 axis value on a CTFont differently from the \u0027size\u0027 of the CTFont. Even CTFontCreateCopyWithAttributes (which promises to preserve the \u0027size\u0027 if the size parameter is 0) will apply a change to the \u0027opsz\u0027 axis and the overwrite it with the \u0027size\u0027.",
      "revId": "318a2d0d12f6db42a7209d8a177a965b115138ec",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
